3. About
--------

citygson is a Java library that provides Java objects for parsing and
serializing CityJSON files. It uses Gson as JSON binding framework.

Feature list:
* Full support for CityJSON version 0.9
* Support for CityJSON extensions

CityJSON is a format for encoding a subset of the CityGML 2.0 data model
using JavaScript Object Notation (JSON) instead of GML. The CityJSON
specification is developed and maintained by the 3D geoinformation group
at TU Delft.


4. System requirements
----------------------

* Java JRE or JDK >= @javaCompatibility@


5. How to use it
----------------

Simply put the @jar@ library file and its mandatory dependencies
from the "lib" folder on your classpath to start developing with citygson.
Have fun :-)

citygson is also available as Maven artifact:

  <dependency>
    <groupId>@groupId@</groupId>
    <artifactId>@artifactId@</artifactId>
    <version>@version@</version>
  </dependency>


